Helm popular repository:-
https://hub.helm.sh/ --official stable repository managed by the Helm community
https://artifacthub.io/ --Community driven repository for Helm charts and other artifacts
https://github.com/bitnami/charts --Helm chart maitained by bitnami for various applications and infrastructure component.


**helm installation command**
$ curl -fsSL -o get_helm.sh https://raw.githubusercontent.com/helm/helm/main/scripts/get-helm-3
$ chmod 700 get_helm.sh
$ ./get_helm.sh

helm create my-chart
helm install my-chart ./my-chart
helm uninstall my-chart


**deploying chart on kubernetes cluster**
helm repo add stable https://charts.helm.sh/stable -- add official stable helm chart repository to local helm setup. it allows 
                                                       to pull application chart from trusted source.
helm search repo stable/mysql                      -- It search local repository for charts related to MYSQL.

kubectl config current-context                     -- show cluster information
kubectl get nodes
helm repo list
helm repo remove repo
helm show chart stable/mysql                       -- metadata about the chart. chart version, app version
helm show readme stable/mysql          
helm show readme stable/mysql >> info.txt         ---this file is readme documentation for Helm chart that installs mysql on k8
                                                     cluster .
                                                     it explain how to install mysql using Helm what k8 version and storage it needs  and how to install and uninstall the mysql database easily.
                                                    it tells you how to use persistent storage for mysql data so data is saved 
                                                    even if the pod restarts, 

helm show values stable/mysql                       -- default conf value for helm chart. kubernetes pod spec like resource limit 
                                                       and probes , service type
helm install mysql stable/mysql --dry-run --debug   -- what would happend when chart is installed.
helm install mysql stable/mysql                    -- install the mysql helm chart into current k8 cluster.
helm list


**Retrieving information about a Release**
helm status mysql
helm get manifest mysql >> mysql.txt     ---get release manifests
helm get values mysql >> values.txt      ---get release values 
helm get notes mysql >> notes.txt        ---get release notes
helm get all mysql                          get all from release
helm history mysql                       ---view release history
helm uninstall mysql --keep-history      ---uninstall a release
helm delete mysql                        ---delete release
helm list --all                          ---confirm with --all flag

